Infotexts.ntg.description.information_aim_latcher_:
A latcher's tongue will always shoot directly forward from your mouth. This means to hit acreature who isn't submerged, they have to be your height to hit them. There are a few tips and tricks to help you aim the tongue on land, however:
- If a creature if half your height, you can crouch to lower your head, allowing you to hit lower targets;
- When you run your head aims down, meaning you shoot at a downward angle as well Crouching and walking backwards slightly raises your head, allowing you to shoot upwards;
- If you are in the water, simply swimming in a way to make your face point your target will let you shoot in any given direction.
